  schema:name "Cybernetics and Governance: Feedback, Variety, and Self-Regulation" ;
  schema:description "How systems theory and cybernetics reframe governance as continuous feedback, adaptation, and the regulation of complexity — a tradition absent from current governance formalism but essential to understanding how actual institutions remain viable." ;
